&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Children’s Social Worker (level 1 or 2) C137 CHSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Norfolk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Up to £34,728 + £2k welcome payment (subject to qualifying criteria)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent relocation package&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to join a dedicated team of social work professionals who are extremely friendly and supportive? Look no further. Our team here in West Norfolk are looking to welcome a qualified social worker to join us in delivering the very best for the children and families of Norfolk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our social care academy will support you to be the best you can be, placing practitioners and relationship-based practice at the heart of what we do. Through Vital Signs, our vision for Children in Norfolk, we use Signs of Safety practice to work with whole family networks, and across the whole system to support families to build on their strengths and to achieve the best possible outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Norfolk is a beautiful part of Norfolk with a stunning coastline and the seaport town of Kings Lynn at its heart. Kings Lynn offers an array of shops and restaurants with direct rail access to London Kings Cross. The area borders the counties of Lincolnshire and Cambridgeshire providing easy access to the North and London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re an experienced children’s social worker and want to work together with us to shape the future of Children’s Services in Norfolk, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;APPLY TO BE A SOCIAL WORKER &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IN WEST NORFOLK TODAY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information on the roles available in West Norfolk please contact Matthew Reading (Head of Social Work, FAST West) on 01553 407096 or matthew.reading@norfolk.gov.uk&lt;/p&gt;
